<h3 id=3D"CodingGuidance-Why?"><strong>Why?</strong></h3>
<p>This stage produces the code that turns client requirements and features=
, into working applications and the automated tests that ensure the applica=
tions are working as expected.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3 id=3D"CodingGuidance-How?"><strong>How?</strong></h3>
<p>Create code and automation code&nbsp;</p>
<p>Have your peers review your code prior to being committed.&nbsp;</p>
<p>During the sprint, teams will be coding for the application, and buildin=
g up the functionality and automated test suite for the application.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Process: Code &gt; Perform Code Analysis &gt; Perform Code Reviews &gt; =
Add Automated Tests</p>
<h3 id=3D"CodingGuidance-QualityGates"><strong>Quality Gates</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li>Code Analysis</li>
<li>Code Review&nbsp;conducted</li>
<li>Security Code Review conducted (if applicable)<br><br></li>
</ul>
