<h1 id=3D"CodingGuidance-CodeAnalysis"><strong>Code Analysis</strong></h1>
<h3 id=3D"CodingGuidance-StaticCodeAnalysis">Static Code Analysis</h3>
<p>Static Analysis is the&nbsp;<a class=3D"external-link" title=3D"Program =
analysis (computer science)" href=3D"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Program_a=
nalysis_(computer_science)" rel=3D"nofollow">analysis of computer software<=
/a>&nbsp;that is performed without actually executing programs (analysis pe=
rformed on executing programs is known as&nbsp;<a title=3D"Dynamic program =
analysis" href=3D"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dynamic_program_analysis" cl=
ass=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">dynamic analysis</a>).In most cases =
the analysis is performed on some version of the&nbsp;<a title=3D"Source co=
de" href=3D"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Source_code" class=3D"external-lin=
k" rel=3D"nofollow">source code</a>, and in the other cases, some form of t=
he&nbsp;<a title=3D"Object code" href=3D"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Objec=
t_code" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">object code</a>. The term =
is usually applied to the analysis performed by an&nbsp;<a title=3D"List of=
 tools for static code analysis" href=3D"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_=
of_tools_for_static_code_analysis" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow"=
>automated tool</a>, with human analysis being called program understanding=
,&nbsp;<a title=3D"Program comprehension" href=3D"http://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/Program_comprehension" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">program=
 comprehension</a>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<a title=3D"Code review" href=3D"http://en.=
wikipedia.org/wiki/Code_review" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">co=
de review</a>.</p>
<p>Examples:&nbsp;</p>
<ul>
<li><a href=3D"http://sonar/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Sona=
rQube</a>&nbsp;has been identified as an automatic static analysis tool tha=
t has been put in place for our teams to use. Teams will need to work with =
QAPOW and the KeyMasters to configure their source code repositories to be =
statically analyzed on a regular basis.</li>
<li>PHPCS / PDepend / PHPMD /&nbsp;<a href=3D"http://hacklang.org/" class=
=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Hack</a>&nbsp;(PHP)</li>
<li>Dialyzer (Erlang)</li>
<li><a href=3D"https://code.facebook.com/posts/1505962329687926/flow-a-new-=
static-type-checker-for-javascript/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollo=
w">Flow</a>&nbsp;(JavaScript)</li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"CodingGuidance-DynamicCodeAnalysis">Dynamic Code Analysis</h3>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102);">Dynamic code analysis&nbsp;relies =
on studying how the code behaves during execution.&nbsp;Dynamic code review=
 has the ability to find security issues caused by the code's interaction w=
ith other system components like SQL databases, application servers or Web =
services. It must be performed by a tool that can understand the language t=
he application is written in.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102);">List of <a href=3D"https://www.pee=
rlyst.com/posts/resource-a-list-of-dynamic-analysis-tools-for-software-susa=
n-parker" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">tools</a> that can be us=
ed for Dynamic Code Analysis</span></p>
</div>=20
