<h1 id=3D"CodingGuidance-CodeReview"><strong>Code Review</strong></h1>
<p>Code Reviews are a critical development practice, which helps to maintai=
n the greatest levels of software quality. It is&nbsp;not just about findin=
g defects/issues with code, it helps transfer knowledge and team communicat=
ion/collaboration.</p>
<p>After a developer is done with their changes for a particular story/feat=
ure, they get it reviewed by another team on the team or anyone else that k=
nows that code well. The reviewer reviews code and makes sure the code has =
been written following standards and guidelines and also that the changes d=
o not have any unintended consequences. If the reviewer finds any problems,=
 the developer makes those changes. Code review is a very important process=
 and makes sure every line of code change has been looked at and approved b=
y someone else.&nbsp;</p>
</div>=20
</div>=20
</div>=20
