<h1 id=3D"CodingGuidance-CodingforAutomatedTesting"><strong>Coding for Auto=
mated Testing</strong></h1>
<p>Teams will begin creating various types of automated tests: Unit, databa=
se, integration, performance, security, etc.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Automated software testing is important due to following reasons:&nbsp;<=
/p>
<ul class=3D"checklist" style=3D"margin-left: 20.0px;">
<li>Manual Testing of all work flows, all fields, including all negative sc=
enarios&nbsp;can be time and cost consuming</li>
<li>Automation increases speed of test execution</li>
<li>Automation helps increase Test Coverage</li>
<li>Manual Testing can become boring and hence error prone</li>
<li>Once the test suite is automated, no human intervention is required. Te=
am members can also run automated tests unattended (overnight)</li>
<li><p>Successive development cycles will also require execution of the sam=
e test suites repeatedly</p></li>
</ul>
<p>The "Goal of Automation" is to reduce number of test cases to be run man=
ually, not eliminate manual testing all together; however, it does free up =
our team members to focus each sprint on ensuring new features, and more ex=
ploratory testing, (and not spending time on repeating manual regression te=
sting each and every sprint).</p>
<h3 id=3D"CodingGuidance-WhichTestCasestoAutomate?">Which Test Cases to Aut=
omate?</h3>
<p>Test cases to be automated can be selected using the following criterion=
:</p>
<ul class=3D"checklist" style=3D"margin-left: 20.0px;">
<li>High Risk - Business Critical test cases</li>
<li>Test cases that are executed repeatedly</li>
<li>Test Cases that are very tedious or difficult to perform manually</li>
<li>Test Cases which are time consuming</li>
</ul>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The following category of test cases are not suitable for automation:</p=
>
<ul class=3D"checklist" style=3D"margin-left: 20.0px;">
<li>Test Cases that are newly designed and not executed manually (at least =
once, for understanding + ensuring correctly implemented functionality)</li=
>
<li>Test Cases for which the requirements are changing frequently</li>
<li>Test cases which are executed on ad-hoc basis</li>
<li>Test cases that have difficult data scenarios (set-up / clean-up)</li>
</ul>
<p>More automation resources are available <a href=3D"https://confluence/di=
splay/IC/Automation+Resources" rel=3D"nofollow">here</a></p>
</div>=20
